annotationA: N6-(1,2-dicarboxyethyl)AMP AMP-lyase (fumarate-forming) activity. It is involved in the biological process described with: purine ribonucleotide biosynthetic process; purine nucleotide metabolic process; Belongs to the lyase 1 family. Adenylosuccinate lyase subfamily
annotationB: Adenylosuccinate synthetase; Plays an important role in the de novo pathway and in the salvage pathway of purine nucleotide biosynthesis. Catalyzes the first committed step in the biosynthesis of AMP from IMP (By similarity). Plays a role in the regulation of adult life span
